The paper deals with online convex optimization, which is a subfield of machine learning and optimization. Specifically, it focuses on adaptivity to Lipschitz and comparator norms, which are important concepts in optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in its analysis of the algorithms' performance. Additionally, the paper deals with the range ratio problem, which is a topic in computational geometry and data structures (cs.DS). The paper's application to online prediction with linear models suggests that it may also fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
